title: Roads: Six miles of queues after accident on M11 at Harlow | Anglia
text:
There are tailbacks of up to six miles on the M11 southbound after an accident which happened at around 6.30am this morning involving two vans.
It happened between J8 for Bishop's Stortford and J7 for Harlow.
The road was closed off for around 15 minutes just before 7am, but then two lanes were re-opened.
There is currently still one lane blocked.
Last updated Mon 17 Aug 2015 Travel Hertfordshire Essex
